						               													<description>Card game for the whole family; each player takes on the role of a powerful (but greedy) Leader in a Kingdom of Adventurers, who through cunning, courage and luck, sends his minions in search of fame and riches.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Suitable for all ages 6 and up, 2 to 6 players. A game can last from 20 to 30 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game based on luck, but that requires a good level of tactics, skill and synergy to be mastered and dominate your minions!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to get 10 Treasure Tokens wins the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are two decks with two different Backs, called Adventure Deck and Adventurer Deck; divide them, shuffle the cards of each deck so that each game is different from the previous ones, keep them face down and place the two separate decks in the center of the table.&amp;#10;Each player draws 3 cards from the Adventurers deck. Also distribute 3 Supply Tokens(ST) to each player, represented by the Food image.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Procedure: The game is divided into rounds, at the beginning of each round the Adventure is determined by the top card of the corresponding deck. Don't reveal it yet, the only information you will have will be the Difficulty level, given by the number on the back of the card ranging from 1 to 3.&amp;#10;Warning, Lv 3 Adventures give more rewards but also hide traps!&amp;#10;After evaluating at the beginning of each turn whether to participate in that specific adventure, players can put one or more Adventurer Cards from their hand onto the field, initially face down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
